Class Portal

java.lang.Object
com.tron_master.tron.model.object.GameObject
com.tron_master.tron.model.object.Wall
com.tron_master.tron.model.object.Portal
public class Portal extends Wall
A portal wall that teleports players to a linked exit portal instead of killing them. Used in Story mode for level design variety. This is a one-way portal: entrance teleports to exit, but exit acts as a normal wall. The entrance portal has the same color as the player (cyan), and the exit has a different color.

  • Method Details

    • linkToExit

      public void linkToExit(Portal exit)
      Links this entrance portal to an exit portal (one-way). Only entrance portals can be linked to exits.
      Parameters:
      exit - The exit portal to link to
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if this portal is not an entrance
      IllegalArgumentException - if exit is not an exit portal

    • teleport

      public boolean teleport(Player player)
      Teleports a player to the linked exit portal's position. Only works for entrance portals with a valid link.
      Parameters:
      player - The player to teleport
      Returns:
      true if teleportation occurred, false if not possible

    • handleCollision

      public boolean handleCollision(Player player)
      Checks if player collides with this portal and handles accordingly. For entrance: teleports player. For exit: acts as normal wall.
      Parameters:
      player - The player to check
      Returns:
      true if player was teleported, false if collision should be handled normally
